False. Orphism, also known as Orphism or Orphic Cubism, was an art movement that emerged from Cubism and was characterized by its use of vibrant colors and abstract forms. Michel Eugène Chevreul was indeed a chemist known for his work on color theory, but Orphism (or Orphismus) is an art movement that was founded by Robert Delaunay and his wife Sonia Delaunay.
